Field Label: Indicates if participant reported symptoms on a 90–180 day follow-up survey.
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1 = PASC+: Indicated symptoms on a followup survey between 90 and 180 days post-infection. 0 = PASC-: NO symptoms on a followup survey in that period. 99 = PASCUnk: No followup survey in time frame.

Field Label: Indicates if participant reported symptoms on a 181–365 day follow-up survey.
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1 = PASC+: Symptoms at 181–365 days AND at 90–180 days. 0 = PASC-: NO symptoms at 181–365 days. 99 = PASCUnk: No followup survey in time frame. 3 = PASCResurge: Symptoms at 181–365 days, not at 90–180. 2 = PASC+QC: Symptoms at 181–365 days, missing 90–180 day survey.

Field Label: Indicates if the participant indicated symptoms on an eligible (between 366 and 548 day) followup survey
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1 = PASC+: Indicated symptoms on a followup survey between 366 and 548 days post- infection AND on a followup survey between 90-180 daysAND on a followup between 181 and 365 days., 0 = PASC-:Indicated NO symptoms on a followup survey between 366 and 548 days post- infection. Regardless or prior infection status, 99 = PASCUnk: Not applicable (participant did not complete a followup survey in the time frame OR Indicated symptoms on a followup survey between 366 and 548 days post-infection but did not have enough prior record to determine status)., 2 = PASC+QC :Indicated symptoms on a followup survey between 366 and 548 days post- infection AND was considered Resurge, PosQC or Unknown followup between 181 and 365 days.
